":"The explode made in [src/Repositories/TestRepository.php#L53](https://github.com/pestphp/pest/blob/master/src/Repositories/TestRepository.php#L53) based on the `@` character prevent usage of plugins when there already is an `@` in the folder absolute path.\r\n\r\nFor example, I am getting the following error when using the snapshot plugin in a project located in `/Users/<username>/Dev/@namespace/project`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  Call to undefined method PHPUnit\\Framework\\TestCase::assertMatchesSnapshot()\r\n\r\n  at vendor/spatie/pest-plugin-snapshots/src/Functions.php:14\r\n     10▕ Plugin::uses(MatchesSnapshots::class);\r\n     11▕ \r\n     12▕ function assertMatchesSnapshot($actual, Driver $driver = null): void\r\n     13▕ {\r\n  ➜  14▕     test()->assertMatchesSnapshot(...func_get_args());\r\n     15▕ }\r\n     16▕ \r\n     17▕ function assertMatchesFileHashSnapshot(string $filePath): void\r\n     18▕ {\r\n```\r\n\r\nI was able to quickly fix this by changing the `@` use as a separator in the test keys to a more specific value `@@@@`. I can open a PR with my fix if needed.\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"lukeraymonddowning","id":12202279,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyMjAyMjc5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/12202279?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukeraymonddowning","html_url":"https://github.com/lukeraymonddowning","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukeraymonddowning/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukeraymonddowning/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukeraymonddowning/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukeraymonddowning/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukeraymonddowning/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukeraymonddowning/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukeraymonddowning/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukeraymonddowning/even